# https://blog.csdn.net/weixin_38646522/article/details/86095200
img2 = img.copy()
def on_EVENT_LBUTTONDOWN(event, x, y, flags, param):
    if event == cv2.EVENT_LBUTTONDOWN:
        xy = "%d,%d" % (x, y)
        cv2.circle(img2, (x, y), 1, (255, 0, 0), thickness=-1)
        cv2.putText(img2, xy, (x, y), cv2.FONT_HERSHEY_PLAIN,
                    1.0, (0, 0, 0), thickness=1)
        cv2.imshow("image", img2)
    
cv2.namedWindow("image")
cv2.setMouseCallback("image", on_EVENT_LBUTTONDOWN)
cv2.imshow("image", img2)
cv2.waitKey(0)
cv2.destroyAllWindows()
In[11]:
img2 = img.copy()
def on_EVENT_LBUTTONDOWN(event, x, y, flags, param):
    global pt1, pt2
    if event == cv2.EVENT_LBUTTONDOWN:
        pt1 = (x, y)
        cv2.circle(img2, (x, y), 10, (255, 0, 0), thickness=-1)
        cv2.imshow("image", img2)
    if event == cv2.EVENT_LBUTTONUP:
        pt2 = (x, y)
        cv2.circle(img2, (x, y), 10, (255, 0, 0), thickness=-1)
        cv2.rectangle(img2, pt1, pt2, (0,0,255), 10)
        cv2.imshow("image", img2)
    
cv2.namedWindow("image")
cv2.setMouseCallback("image", on_EVENT_LBUTTONDOWN)
cv2.imshow("image", img2)
cv2.waitKey(0)
cv2.destroyAllWindows()

cap = cv2.VideoCapture(0)  # 

while (1):
    # get a frame
    ret, frame = cap.read()
    frame = cv2.flip(frame, 1)  # 
    # show a frame
    cv2.imshow("capture", frame)  # 

    if cv2.waitKey(1) & 0xFF == ord('q'):  # q 
#         cv2.imwrite("test.png", frame)  # 
        break

cap.release()
cv2.destroyAllWindows()

cap = cv2.VideoCapture("sample.mp4")

while (1):
    # get a frame
    ret, frame = cap.read()
#     frame = cv2.flip(frame, 1)  # 
    # show a frame
    faces = face_detector.detectMultiScale(frame,1.01,10)
    for x,y,w,h in faces:
        cv2.rectangle(frame,(x,y),(x+w,y+h),(255,0,0),2)
    cv2.imshow("capture", frame)  # 

    if cv2.waitKey(1) & 0xFF == ord('q'):  # q 
#         cv2.imwrite("test.png", frame)  # 
        break

cap.release()

# model = cv2.face.FisherFaceRecognizer_create()
# model = cv2.face.LBPHFaceRecognizer_create()

img1 = cv2.resize(img_c, dsize=[160,160])
img2 = cv2.resize(img_c, dsize=[160,160])
img3 = cv2.resize(img_replace, dsize=[160,160])
img_l = [img1]*9 + [img3]*9 + [img2, img3]
labels = np.append([1]*9 + [2]*9, [1, 2])


# 
# LBPH
model.train(img_l, labels)
# confidence :
# 0020000,5000 ,
# ,LBPH50,85
